  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why does Quora mobile app use so much data?",
  "response": "The Quora mobile app may consume a significant amount of data due to several factors:\n\n1. **Streaming and Loading Content:** Quora continuously loads new questions, answers, and advertisements as you scroll through your feed. This includes images, videos, and other media that can quickly add up in terms of data usage.\n\n2. **High-Quality Images and Videos:** If you have your device settings configured to load high-quality media, this can significantly increase data consumption. Videos, in particular, can use a large amount of data, especially if they are set to autoplay.\n\n3. **Background Data Usage:** The app may use data in the background to refresh content, send notifications, and synchronize data. This can occur even when you're not actively using the app.\n\n4. **Advertisements:** Quora displays ads, which contribute to data usage. The more ads that are loaded, the more data is used.\n\n5. **User Activity:** The more you use the app, the more data it will consume. This includes actions like searching for topics, following new questions, and engaging with content.\n\nTo manage data usage on the Quora app, consider the following:\n\n- **Use Wi-Fi:** When possible, connect to Wi-Fi to reduce mobile data usage.\n- **Adjust Media Settings:** Lower the quality of images and videos or disable autoplay.\n- **Limit Background Data:** Go to your device settings and restrict background data usage for the Quora app.\n- **Monitor Usage:** Keep an eye on your data usage through your device's settings to understand how much the Quora app is consuming.\n\nBy implementing these strategies, you can better manage and potentially reduce the amount of data the Quora mobile app uses.",
